{"event": "tool_result", "tool": "view", "is_error": false, "result": {"status": "success", "file": "C:\\QAx\\002\\artifacts\\outputs\\product-definition\\epics\\EPICS-SPEC-EPICS-STARWARSLEGO-PRODUCTDEFINITION-20260703.md", "content": "1: ---\n2: version: 1.0.0\n3: session_id: EPICS-STARWARSLEGO-PRODUCTDEFINITION-20260703\n4: engagement_mode: greenfield\n5: skill: planning-epics\n6: generated_at: 2026-07-03T15:35:00.000Z\n7: ---\n8: \n9: # EPICS SPEC: Star Wars Lego Educational Web Application\n10: \n11: ## Themes\n12: \n13: ### THM-01: User Interface and Interaction\n14: **Description:** Core visual components and interactive behaviors for the character gallery.\n15: **Source FRs:** FR-01, FR-07\n16: **Source NFRs:** NFR-03, NFR-04, NFR-08\n17: **KPI Alignment:** KPI-01, KPI-02\n18: \n19: ### THM-02: Search and Discovery\n20: **Description:** Character filtering, search functionality, and data management operations.\n21: **Source FRs:** FR-02, FR-03, FR-04\n22: **Source NFRs:** NFR-07\n23: **KPI Alignment:** KPI-03\n24: \n25: ### THM-03: Personalization and User Experience\n26: **Description:** Custom user preferences, dynamic content, and personalized interactions.\n27: **Source FRs:** FR-05, FR-06\n28: **KPI Alignment:** KPI-01, KPI-02\n29: \n30: ### THM-04: Technical Excellence and Performance\n31: **Description:** Browser compatibility, security, performance standards, and code quality.\n32: **Source NFRs:** NFR-01, NFR-02, NFR-05, NFR-06\n33: **KPI Alignment:** KPI-04, KPI-05\n34: \n35: ## Epics\n36: \n37: ### EPIC-01: Character Gallery Foundation\n38: **Type:** feature\n39: **Theme:** THM-01\n40: **Priority:** Must Have\n41: **Size:** M\n42: **Source FRs:** FR-01, FR-07\n43: **Source NFRs:** NFR-03, NFR-04\n44: **KPI Alignment:** KPI-01, KPI-02\n45: **JTBD Alignment:** JTBD-01, JTBD-03, JTBD-04, JTBD-05, JTBD-06\n46: **Business Value:** Interactive character display enables hands-on JavaScript learning through visual DOM manipulation and component interaction patterns.\n47: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n48: - Grid-based layout displays 8 Star Wars Lego characters\n49: - Hover effects trigger smooth CSS transitions at 60fps\n50: - Character selection highlights individual cards and shows detailed information\n51: - All interactions function across Chrome 90+, Firefox 88+, Safari 14+, Edge 90+\n52: \n53: ### EPIC-02: Real-time Search and Filter Engine\n54: **Type:** feature\n55: **Theme:** THM-02\n56: **Priority:** Must Have\n57: **Size:** S\n58: **Source FRs:** FR-02\n59: **Source NFRs:** NFR-07\n60: **KPI Alignment:** KPI-03\n61: **JTBD Alignment:** JTBD-01, JTBD-05\n62: **Business Value:** Instant character filtering demonstrates JavaScript ES6+ array methods and reactive data binding patterns in practical scenarios.\n63: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n64: - Real-time filtering responds to typing with <100ms latency\n65: - Input validation prevents empty search submissions\n66: - Search functionality works across all supported browsers\n67: - Filter results update character display without full page reload\n68: \n69: ### EPIC-03: Character Interaction Management\n70: **Type:** feature\n71: **Theme:** THM-02\n72: **Priority:** Should Have\n73: **Size:** M\n74: **Source FRs:** FR-03, FR-04\n75: **KPI Alignment:** KPI-01, KPI-02\n76: **JTBD Alignment:** JTBD-01, JTBD-02, JTBD-05\n77: **Business Value:** Like/favorite systems and deletion controls teach state management and Vue.js reactivity concepts through user-driven data changes.\n78: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n79: - Toggle favorite status with persistent visual feedback during session\n80: - Character deletion includes confirmation and visual confirmation feedback\n81: - All preference changes trigger immediate UI updates\n82: - Deleted characters remain hidden during current session\n83: \n84: ### EPIC-04: Dynamic Personalization System\n85: **Type:** feature\n86: **Theme:** THM-03\n87: **Priority:** Could Have\n88: **Size:** S\n89: **Source FRs:** FR-05, FR-06\n90: **KPI Alignment:** KPI-01\n91: **JTBD Alignment:** JTBD-01, JTBD-02\n92: **Business Value:** Personalized greetings and dynamic titles demonstrate JavaScript event handling and DOM manipulation based on user activity tracking.\n93: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n94: - Greeting messages update based on significant user interactions\n95: - Browser tab title reflects current application context\n96: - Custom greeting input persists during session\n97: - All dynamic updates occur without page refresh\n98: \n99: ### EPIC-05: Cross-Browser Technical Foundation\n100: **Type:** enabler\n101: **Theme:** THM-04\n102: **Priority:** Must Have\n103: **Size:** L\n104: **Source NFRs:** NFR-01, NFR-02, NFR-05, NFR-06\n105: **KPI Alignment:** KPI-04, KPI-05\n106: **Business Value:** Technical foundation ensures consistent educational experience across all target browsers and meets security standards for educational content delivery.\n107: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n108: - Application loads in <3 seconds across all supported browsers\n109: - OWASP Top 10 compliance verified through static analysis\n110: - Code achieves 90%+ documentation coverage with modular structure\n111: - Progressive enhancement maintains functionality when features unavailable\n112: \n113: ### EPIC-06: Performance and Animation Optimization\n114: **Type:** enabler\n115: **Theme:** THM-04\n116: **Priority:** Should Have\n117: **Size:** M\n118: **Source NFRs:** NFR-04, NFR-08\n119: **KPI Alignment:** KPI-04\n120: **Business Value:** Optimized animations and performance profiling demonstrate JavaScript performance optimization techniques essential for production applications.\n121: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n122: - All CSS transitions maintain 60fps on target devices\n123: - Design system achieves 100% compliance with specified visual standards\n124: - Performance profiling identifies and resolves bottlenecks\n125: - Visual regression testing maintains consistency across viewport sizes\n126: \n127: ## Dependencies\n128: \n129: ### Direct Dependencies\n130: | Epic | Depends On | Type | Rationale |\n131: |------|------------|------|-----------|\n132: | EPIC-01 | EPIC-05 | blocking | Character gallery requires cross-browser foundation to function consistently |\n133: | EPIC-02 | EPIC-01 | functional | Search functionality operates on characters displayed in gallery |\n134: | EPIC-03 | EPIC-01 | functional | Character interactions require character gallery to be available |\n135: | EPIC-03 | EPIC-05 | functional | Browser compatibility required for consistent interaction behavior |\n136: | EPIC-04 | EPIC-01 | functional | Personalization features respond to character/gallery interactions |\n137: | EPIC-04 | EPIC-03 | functional | Personalized greetings track character interaction events |\n138: | EPIC-06 | EPIC-01 | functional | Animation optimization applies to gallery visual effects |\n139: | EPIC-06 | EPIC-05 | functional | Performance optimization requires browser compatibility baseline |\n140: \n141: ### Dependency Graph\n142: ```\n143: EPIC-05 (Cross-Browser Foundation)\n144: ├── EPIC-01 (Character Gallery)\n145: │   ├── EPIC-02 (Search Engine)\n146: │   ├── EPIC-03 (Interaction Management)\n147: │   │   └── EPIC-04 (Personalization)\n148: │   └── EPIC-06 (Performance Optimization)\n149: ```\n150: \n151: ### Circular Dependencies\n152: **Status:** No circular dependencies detected\n153: \n154: ### External Dependencies\n155: | Dependency | Impact | Mitigation |\n156: |------------|--------|------------|\n157: | Vue.js 2.x Framework | Application functionality | Include local library fallback |\n158: | Google Fonts CDN | Visual design enhancement | System font fallbacks |\n159: | Material Symbols | User interface clarity | Text alternatives |\n160: | Internet Connectivity | External resource loading | Graceful degradation |\n161: \n162: ## Sequencing\n163: \n164: ### Topological Order\n165: | Wave | Epic | Priority | Dependencies | Rationale |\n166: |------|------|----------|--------------|-----------|\n167: | Wave 1 | EPIC-05 | Must Have | None | Foundation epic enables all other functionality |\n168: | Wave 1 | EPIC-01 | Must Have | EPIC-05 | Core feature deliverable, blocks multiple other epics |\n169: | Wave 2 | EPIC-02 | Must Have | EPIC-01 | Essential search functionality, dependency satisfied |\n170: | Wave 2 | EPIC-03 | Should Have | EPIC-01, EPIC-05 | Interaction features extend core gallery |\n171: | Wave 2 | EPIC-06 | Should Have | EPIC-01, EPIC-05 | Performance optimization for existing features |\n172: | Wave 3 | EPIC-04 | Could Have | EPIC-01, EPIC-03 | Enhancement features, highest dependency chain |\n173: \n174: ### Dependency Validation\n175: **Status:** No blocked epic scheduled before its blocker\n176: **Validation:** All dependency relationships respected in topological order\n177: \n178: ### Implementation Phases\n179: #### Phase 1: Foundation (Core Educational Value)\n180: - EPIC-05: Cross-Browser Technical Foundation\n181: - EPIC-01: Character Gallery Foundation\n182: - EPIC-02: Real-time Search and Filter Engine\n183: \n184: #### Phase 2: Enhancement (Interactive Engagement)\n185: - EPIC-03: Character Interaction Management\n186: - EPIC-06: Performance and Animation Optimization\n187: \n188: #### Phase 3: Advanced Features (Personalization)\n189: - EPIC-04: Dynamic Personalization System\n190: \n191: ### Sequencing Rationale\n192: - **Foundation First:** Cross-browser foundation (EPIC-05) enables consistent delivery\n193: - **Core Features First:** Character gallery (EPIC-01) and search (EPIC-02) deliver primary educational value\n194: - **Progressive Enhancement:** Later waves build upon solid foundation\n195: - **Risk Mitigation:** Higher priority items completed before lower risk features\n196: \n197: ### MVP Alignment\n198: **Phase 0 Corresponds to:** Wave 1 (EPIC-05, EPIC-01, EPIC-02)\n199: **Phase 1 Corresponds to:** Wave 2 (EPIC-03, EPIC-06)  \n200: **Phase 2 Corresponds to:** Wave 3 (EPIC-04)\n201: \n202: ## Reclassification Log\n203: \n204: ### Qualification Gate Results\n205: | Candidate ID | Gate 1 (Deliverable) | Gate 2 (NFR Overlap) | Gate 3 (Enabler) | Final Classification | Rationale |\n206: |--------------|---------------------|---------------------|------------------|-------------------|-----------|\n207: | Character Gallery Foundation | PASS | PASS | FAIL | feature | Discrete deliverable with interactive functionality |\n208: | Search Engine | PASS | PASS | FAIL | feature | Standalone search functionality |\n209: | Interaction Management | PASS | PASS | FAIL | feature | User interactions with character data |\n210: | Personalization System | PASS | PASS | FAIL | feature | User preference customization features |\n211: | Browser Foundation | FAIL | FAIL | PASS | enabler | Technical infrastructure, no direct user value |\n212: | Performance Optimization | FAIL | FAIL | PASS | enabler | Technical improvement, infrastructure focus |\n213: \n214: ### Gate Analysis\n215: **Gate 1 - Discrete Deliverable Test:** 4 passed, 2 failed\n216: - FAILED: EPIC-05, EPIC-06 classified as enablers (infrastructure focus)\n217: - PASSED: All feature epics provide demonstrable user value\n218: \n219: **Gate 2 - NFR Overlap Test:** 4 passed, 2 failed  \n220: - FAILED: EPIC-05, EPIC-06 scope equals multiple NFRs (browser compatibility, performance)\n221: - PASSED: Feature epics implement NFRs as constraints rather than primary scope\n222: \n223: **Gate 3 - Enabler vs Feature Test:** 2 enablers identified\n224: - PASSED: EPIC-05, EPIC-06 properly classified as enablers with KPI alignment\n225: - All enablers trace to KPI-04 (Performance Accessibility) and KPI-05 (Browser Coverage)\n226: \n227: ### Reclassification Decisions\n228: **No reclassification required:** All candidates passed appropriate qualification gates\n229: **Zero circular dependencies:** No enabler extraction needed\n230: **Alignment validation:** All epics have proper FR/NFR/JTBD/KPI traceability\n231: \n232: ### Quality Checks\n233: - EPIC sizing distribution: 1 XS, 2 S, 2 M, 1 L (no XL oversized epics)\n234: - Priority distribution: 3 Must Have, 2 Should Have, 1 Could Have\n235: - Type distribution: 4 features, 2 enablers, 0 spikes\n236: - All business values traceable to JTBDs or KPIs\n237: \n238: ## Persona Coverage\n239: \n240: ### P-01: Beginner JavaScript Student\n241: **Serving Epics:** EPIC-01, EPIC-02, EPIC-03, EPIC-04, EPIC-05, EPIC-06\n242: **Primary Value:** Hands-on JavaScript learning through interactive character manipulation\n243: **Coverage Analysis:** 100% coverage - All epics support beginner learning objectives\n244: **Key Features:** Gallery interactions, search functionality, state management examples\n245: \n246: ### P-02: Web Development Learner  \n247: **Serving Epics:** EPIC-01, EPIC-02, EPIC-03, EPIC-05, EPIC-06\n248: **Primary Value:** Practical Vue.js and modern JavaScript framework experience\n249: **Coverage Analysis:** 83% coverage - Personalization (EPIC-04) less relevant for portfolio building\n250: **Key Features:** Component patterns, reactive data binding, performance optimization techniques\n251: \n252: ### P-03: Programming Educator\n253: **Serving Epics:** EPIC-01, EPIC-02, EPIC-05\n254: **Primary Value:** Teaching demonstrations and classroom presentation tools\n255: **Coverage Analysis:** 50% coverage - Focus on core interactive elements for teaching\n256: **Key Features:** Visual examples, cross-browser reliability for classroom use\n257: \n258: ### Coverage Summary\n259: | Persona | Epics Covered | Coverage % | Gaps Identified |\n260: |---------|---------------|------------|-----------------|\n261: | P-01 (Beginner Student) | 6/6 | 100% | None |\n262: | P-02 (Web Learner) | 5/6 | 83% | EPIC-04 less relevant |\n263: | P-03 (Educator) | 3/6 | 50% | Focus on core teaching features |\n264: \n265: ### Coverage Validation\n266: **Status:** All personas have minimum 1 epic coverage requirement satisfied\n267: **Gaps:** No critical gaps - reduced relevance for certain secondary features expected\n268: **Distribution:** Balanced coverage across primary learning objectives\n269: \n270: ## Goal Coverage\n271: \n272: ### JTBD Coverage Analysis\n273: | JTBD ID | Description | Supporting Epics | Coverage Status |\n274: |---------|-------------|------------------|----------------|\n275: | JTBD-01 | Learn JavaScript Fundamentals | EPIC-01, EPIC-02, EPIC-03, EPIC-04 | FULL |\n276: | JTBD-02 | Understand Vue.js Reactivity | EPIC-03, EPIC-04 | FULL |\n277: | JTBD-03 | Practice DOM Manipulation | EPIC-01, EPIC-04 | FULL |\n278: | JTBD-04 | Demonstrate Programming Concepts | EPIC-01, EPIC-02, EPIC-05 | FULL |\n279: | JTBD-05 | Apply ES6+ Features Practically | EPIC-01, EPIC-02, EPIC-03 | FULL |\n280: | JTBD-06 | Create Portfolio-Worthy Projects | EPIC-01, EPIC-03, EPIC-06 | FULL |\n281: \n282: ### KPI Coverage Analysis\n283: | KPI ID | Description | Supporting Epics | Measurement Approach |\n284: |---------|-------------|------------------|---------------------|\n285: | KPI-01 | Learning Engagement Rate | EPIC-01, EPIC-03, EPIC-04 | Track user interactions per session |\n286: | KPI-02 | Concept Demonstration Effectiveness | EPIC-01, EPIC-03, EPIC-04 | Track completion of interaction cycles |\n287: | KPI-03 | Search Functionality Usage | EPIC-02 | Track search queries per session |\n288: | KPI-04 | Performance Accessibility | EPIC-05, EPIC-06 | Load time compliance monitoring |\n289: | KPI-05 | Browser Compatibility Coverage | EPIC-05 | Cross-browser testing success rate |\n290: | KPI-06 | Code Learning Retention | EPIC-01, EPIC-03 | Return visit frequency tracking |\n291: \n292: ### FR Coverage Mapping\n293: | FR ID | Title | Covering Epic(s) | Coverage Status |\n294: |-------|-------|------------------|----------------|\n295: | FR-01 | Character Gallery Display | EPIC-01 | FULL |\n296: | FR-02 | Character Search System | EPIC-02 | FULL |\n297: | FR-03 | Character Like/Favorite System | EPIC-03 | FULL |\n298: | FR-04 | Character Deletion System | EPIC-03 | FULL |\n299: | FR-05 | Personalized Greeting System | EPIC-04 | FULL |\n300: | FR-06 | Dynamic Title Updates | EPIC-04 | FULL |\n301: | FR-07 | Interactive Character Selection | EPIC-01 | FULL |\n302: \n303: ### NFR Coverage Mapping\n304: | NFR ID | Category | Covering Epic(s) | Coverage Status |\n305: |-------|----------|------------------|----------------|\n306: | NFR-01 | Browser Compatibility | EPIC-05 | FULL |\n307: | NFR-02 | Performance Loading Time | EPIC-05 | FULL |\n308: | NFR-03 | Responsive Design | EPIC-01 | FULL |\n309: | NFR-04 | Animation Performance | EPIC-01, EPIC-06 | FULL |\n310: | NFR-05 | Client-Side Security | EPIC-05 | FULL |\n311: | NFR-06 | Code Quality Standards | EPIC-05 | FULL |\n312: | NFR-07 | Search Performance | EPIC-02 | FULL |\n313: | NFR-08 | Visual Design Consistency | EPIC-06 | FULL |\n314: \n315: ### Coverage Validation\n316: **FR Coverage:** 100% (7/7 FRs fully covered)\n317: **NFR Coverage:** 100% (8/8 NFRs fully covered as DoD constraints)\n318: **JTBD Coverage:** 100% (6/6 JTBDs fully addressed)\n319: **KPI Coverage:** 100% (6/6 KPIs measurable through epic implementations)\n320: \n321: **Input/Output Count:** FR coverage: 7 of 7 FRs mapped (100%)\n322: **Coverage Quality:** All requirements mapped with specific acceptance criteria\n323: \n324: ## Open Questions\n325: \n326: ### Carried Forward from PRD\n327: | Question ID | Question | Impact on Epic | Status |\n328: |-------------|----------|----------------|--------|\n329: | OQ-01 | Character Selection Criteria - What specific criteria should be used for selecting the 8 classic Star Wars Lego characters? | EPIC-01 | requires_input |\n330: | OQ-02 | Learning Assessment Methods - How should the application measure and validate that users are actually learning JavaScript concepts? | EPIC-01, EPIC-03, EPIC-04 | requires_input |\n331: | OQ-03 | State Persistence Strategy - Should user preferences (likes, greetings) persist beyond the current session using local storage? | EPIC-03, EPIC-04 | assumption |\n332: | OQ-04 | Character Information Content - What specific information should be displayed for each character when selected (FR-07)? | EPIC-01 | requires_input |\n333: | OQ-05 | Error Handling Scenarios - What specific error scenarios should be anticipated and how should they be handled gracefully? | EPIC-05 | assumption |\n334: \n335: ### Assumptions to Validate\n336: | Assumption ID | Assumption | Impact | Validation Strategy |\n337: |---------------|------------|--------|-------------------|\n338: | ASM-01 | Technical Literacy - Target users have basic computer literacy and can operate web browsers | All epics | user_testing |\n339: | ASM-02 | Internet Access - Users have reliable internet access for loading external resources | EPIC-05, EPIC-06 | fallback_testing |\n340: | ASM-03 | Viewport Availability - Users have access to devices with 820px+ screen resolution | EPIC-01, EPIC-05 | device_testing |\n341: | ASM-04 | JavaScript Interest - Target users are motivated to learn JavaScript programming concepts | EPIC-01, EPIC-03, EPIC-04 | engagement_metrics |\n342: \n343: ### Unresolved Design Decisions\n344: | Decision Area | Required Input | Impact on Epic |\n345: |---------------|----------------|----------------|\n346: | Character Data Model | Character attributes, metadata structure, visual assets | EPIC-01 |\n347: | Search Algorithm | Exact match vs fuzzy matching, case sensitivity, search result ranking | EPIC-02 |\n348: | Animation Specifications | Transition types, duration, easing functions, trigger conditions | EPIC-01, EPIC-06 |\n349: | Progress Tracking | Interaction events to track, data points for KPI measurement | All epics |\n350: \n351: ### Traceability Gaps\n352: **None identified** - All FRs, NFRs, JTBDs, and KPIs have complete traceability through epics\n353: \n354: ### Deferred Items\n355: **None identified** - All PRD requirements included in epic backlog\n356: \n357: ### Blocking Questions\n358: | Question | Blocking Epic(s) | Priority |\n359: |----------|-----------------|----------|\n360: | Character Selection Criteria (OQ-01) | EPIC-01 | HIGH |\n361: | Character Information Content (OQ-04) | EPIC-01 | HIGH |\n362: | Character Data Model | EPIC-01 | HIGH |\n363: | Learning Assessment Methods (OQ-02) | EPIC-01, EPIC-03, EPIC-04 | MEDIUM |\n364: \n365: ### Open Questions Summary\n366: **Total Questions:** 12 (5 carried forward, 4 assumptions, 3 design decisions)\n367: **Blocking Questions:** 4 (high priority for EPIC-01 implementation)\n368: **Non-blocking Assumptions:** 4 (validated during development)", "metadata": {"start_line": 1, "end_line": 368, "returned_lines": 368, "has_more": false, "eof_reached": true, "truncated": false}}}
